                    <xref ref-type="fig" rid="f7">Figure 7</xref>. The highest percentage for EU projects is achieved by the &#x201c;Systemic&#x201d; category (53% of projects) while transnational projects were predominantly made up of the &#x201c;Agroecological transformation&#x201d; category (67%). The &#x201c;Incremental change&#x201d; addressing exclusively the level 1 and/or 2 of food system transformation was only present in the survey open to all agroecology researchers (20% of the cases).</p>
